# Frontend — Component & Styling Patterns

## Component Structure
```tsx
// Named export, props type co-located, no React import needed (Next.js 16)
type CardProps = { title: string; isLoading?: boolean };

export function Card({ title, isLoading = false }: CardProps) {
  if (isLoading) return <CardSkeleton />;
  return <div className="...">{title}</div>;
}
```

- Every data-fetching component MUST handle: loading skeleton, error boundary/message, empty state
- Co-locate sub-components in the same file if under ~80 lines total; extract to own file when larger
- Keep components under 200 lines — extract hooks for logic

## Tailwind v4
- Design tokens defined in `apps/web/src/app/globals.css` via `@theme`
- Colors use CSS custom properties: `hsl(var(--background))`, `hsl(var(--foreground))`
- Mastery colors: `mastery-0` through `mastery-5` (CSS vars, NOT hardcoded hex)
- Dark mode: `next-themes` class strategy — use `.dark` selector in CSS, NOT `dark:` variant on every element when a CSS var suffices

## Fonts
- `font-sans` (Inter) — all UI text
- `font-serif` (Source Serif 4) — AI mentor chat bubbles only
- `font-mono` (JetBrains Mono) — code blocks only

## shadcn/ui Usage
- Import from `@/components/ui/[component]` — never directly from Radix
- Extend with className merging via `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`
- Toasts: `import { toast } from "@/components/ui/sonner"` — no other toast library

## tRPC Data Fetching Pattern
```tsx
// Server component (preferred for initial data)
const data = await trpc.library.list.query();

// Client component
const { data, isLoading, error } = api.library.list.useQuery();
if (isLoading) return <Skeleton />;
if (error) return <ErrorMessage message={error.message} />;
if (!data?.length) return <EmptyState />;
```

## TanStack Query Defaults — REQUIRED
The global `QueryClient` must be configured with these defaults (already set in `apps/web/src/trpc/`):
```ts
defaultOptions: {
  queries: {
    staleTime: 30_000,          // 30s before background refetch
    gcTime: 5 * 60_000,         // 5min before garbage collection
    refetchOnWindowFocus: false, // no refetch on tab switch
  },
}
```
Do NOT override these per-query unless there is a specific real-time requirement (e.g. review queue).

## Animations
Use project-defined keyframes from `globals.css`:
`animate-cursor-blink`, `animate-shimmer`, `animate-level-up`
